## 6. Chrome Pre-warming

### Design

The daemon maintains a "warm pool" of zero or one pre-launched Chromium instance. This is NOT part of the session pool -- it's a separately managed instance that is claimed when a new session starts.

### New Crate: `crates/ans-warmer/`

```rust
// crates/ans-warmer/src/lib.rs

use ans_cdp::CdpBackend;
use ans_stealth::StealthConfig;
use std::sync::Arc;
use tokio::sync::Mutex;

/// A single pre-warmed Chromium instance, ready to be claimed.
pub struct WarmBrowser {
    /// The pre-launched backend. None if not yet launched or already claimed.
    backend: Arc<Mutex<Option<CdpBackend>>>,
}

impl WarmBrowser {
    pub fn new() -> Self {
        Self { backend: Arc::new(Mutex::new(None)) }
    }

    /// Launch Chromium and navigate to about:blank. Called at daemon startup.
    pub async fn warm(&self) -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {
        let backend = CdpBackend::launch(Some(StealthConfig::standard())).await?;
        let _ = backend.navigate("about:blank", std::time::Duration::from_secs(5)).await;
        let mut guard = self.backend.lock().await;
        *guard = Some(backend);
        tracing::info!("Chrome pre-warmed and ready");
        Ok(())
    }

    /// Claim the pre-warmed instance. Returns None if none available.
    /// The caller takes ownership of the CdpBackend.
    pub async fn claim(&self) -> Option<CdpBackend> {
        self.backend.lock().await.take()
    }

    /// Check if a warm instance is available.
    pub async fn is_warm(&self) -> bool {
        self.backend.lock().await.is_some()
    }

    /// Re-warm after an instance was claimed. Called after session closes.
    pub async fn rewarm(&self) {
        if self.backend.lock().await.is_none() {
            match CdpBackend::launch(Some(StealthConfig::standard())).await {
                Ok(backend) => {
                    let _ = backend.navigate("about:blank",
                        std::time::Duration::from_secs(5)).await;
                    *self.backend.lock().await = Some(backend);
                    tracing::info!("Chrome re-warmed");
                }
                Err(e) => {
                    tracing::warn!(%e, "Failed to re-warm Chrome");
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
```

### Session Manager Changes (`session.rs`)

Modify `SessionManager::create()` to accept an optional pre-warmed backend:

```rust
impl SessionManager {
    pub async fn create_with_warm(
        &self,
        goal_id: Uuid,
        start_url: Option<String>,
        warm_backend: Option<CdpBackend>,  // NEW parameter
    ) -> Result<Uuid, BrowserError> {
        let session_id = Uuid::new_v4();

        let backend = if let Some(backend) = warm_backend {
            // Claim the pre-warmed instance -- zero launch time
            backend
        } else {
            // Cold launch
            CdpBackend::launch(Some(StealthConfig::standard())).await?
        };

        // ... rest of session creation identical ...
    }
}
```

### Daemon Changes (`main.rs`)

```rust
#[tokio::main]
async fn main() {
    // ... existing setup ...

    // ── Pre-warm Chrome ─────────────────────────────────
    let warmer = Arc::new(ans_warmer::WarmBrowser::new());
    warmer.warm().await?;  // Launch during startup, ~1.5s

    // ── Start gRPC server ───────────────────────────────
    let server = IpcServer::new()
        .with_nerves_dir(nerves_abs)
        .with_warmer(Arc::clone(&warmer));   // NEW: pass warmer

    // ... rest
}
```

### Lifecycle

```
Daemon startup:
  ├── warmer.warm() → launch Chrome, navigate about:blank
  │
  ├── gRPC server starts
  └── gateway starts

Goal created (create_session gRPC call):
  ├── warmer.claim() → take the CdpBackend
  │   (removes from pool, returns owned backend)
  ├── SessionManager.create_with_warm(warm_backend=Some(claimed))
  │   → session uses the pre-warmed instance, instant start
  └── tokio::spawn(rewarm_task) → warmer.rewarm()
      (launches new warm instance in background)

Goal completed, session closed:
  └── SessionManager.close() kills the used Chrome
      (the warm instance for the NEXT goal is already running)
```

Traffic pattern: Goal 1 starts instantly (pre-warmed Chrome waiting). While Goal 1 runs, a new warm Chrome is launched. When Goal 2 starts, it claims the warm Chrome. The `warm()` call on startup and `rewarm()` after claim keep the pool filled.

### Config: `ans.toml`

```toml
[warmer]
enabled = true         # disable for dev/CI
warm_at_startup = true # launch one Chrome on daemon boot
```

### gRPC Server Wire-up

```rust
// In IpcServer::new() or with_warmer():
pub fn with_warmer(mut self, warmer: Arc<ans_warmer::WarmBrowser>) -> Self {
    self.warmer = Some(warmer);
    self
}

// In create_session handler:
async fn create_session(&self, request: Request<CreateSessionRequest>) -> ... {
    let warm = if let Some(ref w) = self.warmer {
        w.claim().await
    } else {
        None
    };

    let session_id = self.sessions.create_with_warm(goal_id, start_url, warm).await?;

    // After session is created, trigger re-warm in background
    if let Some(ref w) = self.warmer {
        let w = Arc::clone(w);
        tokio::spawn(async move { w.rewarm().await });
    }

    // ... rest of handler ...
}
```

